          <td width="32" background="images/content_left.jpg"></td>
          <td width="689" valign="top" background="images/bg01.jpg"> <p> 
              <B><font color='#FF3300' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif' size='2'>"The Vision," Officially Eradicated - News At 11<BR></B></font><font face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif' size='1'>2002-07-19 04:13:54&nbsp;-&nbsp;<font face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif' size='1'><I>Animal Mother</I>&nbsp;              </font><br>
              <img src="images/content_bar.jpg" width="645" height="1"></p>
            <p>
<font face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif' size='2'>		
I caught up with John Smedley recently and asked him a few questions about the state of the game, check it out!<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: So, how's EQ going?<br />
<br />
Smed: Hrm, haven't had an EQ here in a few<br />
      years. Not any that I could feel anyways.<br />
      I have a California King and it's damn    <br />
      comfy.<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: I was talking about Everquest.<br />
<br />
Smed: I knew that...<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: So, um yea, anyways, so what's<br />
               the future of EQ looking like to<br />
               you?<br />
<br />
Smed: Haha, you're not gonna fool me twice. I <br />
      follow the news, we aren't supposed to <br />
      have any earthquakes down here anytime<br />
      soon.<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: Still talking about Everquest.<br />
<br />
Smed: Why? It's such a nice day. Hot as hell<br />
      though.. kinda dry. Hrm.. Maybe you're<br />
      right; an earthquake may be coming our way.<br />
      Hope my insurance will cover any damages.<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: I'm sure it will. Can we talk<br />
               about your job?<br />
<br />
Smed: Sure.. what's up?<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: Do you feel by opening Legends <br />
               you have totally compromised the <br />
               integrity of the game?<br />
<br />
Smed: Some things are more important than money.<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: Like what?<br />
<br />
Smed: We don't know yet, but when we find out<br />
      we're gonna sell 'em like hotcakes, baby!<br />
<br />
Animal Mother: Thanks for the interview, Smed.<br />
<br />
<br />
______<br />
<br />
More to come....</font>
			
